# grapher_implicit_circle_smoke.numos — Phase 10B. Plot the IMPLICIT equation
# x^2 + y^2 = 1 (a unit circle) and screenshot it. Proves the new implicit-
# equation renderer (marching squares over G(x,y)=lhs-rhs=0, GraphModel +
# GrapherApp::plotImplicit) draws a multi-valued curve the single-valued
# adaptive sampler cannot. Zooms in so the unit circle fills the view.
# Warning-only (screenshot, no golden); NOT CI-gated.
log "implicit circle: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
# down: TAB_BAR -> CONTENT (Add row); enter: addFunction()+startEditing(slot0)
key down
key enter
# Type "x^2+y^2=1". RIGHT exits each exponent superscript back to the row.
key x
key ^
key 2
key right
key +
key y
key ^
key 2
key right
key =
key 1
key enter
wait 80
key graph
wait 80
# TRACE -> NAVIGATE, then zoom in 3x (centered on origin) so the circle is large.
key zoom
key zoom
key zoom
wait 150
screenshot out/grapher_implicit_circle_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "implicit circle: x^2+y^2=1 plotted"
